{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The embedding vector produced for a given query string has the correct dimensionality for the vector database index.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Failure boundary is at the real embedding-model output contract, not just local parsing. A stubbed embedding response can hide real dimension drift (model/version/config mismatch). Behavior text requires the vector be \"produced for a given query string,\" so the real model output shape must be exercised. Rejected lower level (System/Integration): disqualified because those can pass with mocked vectors and miss model-output dimension failures. Rejected higher level (Workflow): disqualified by behavior scope; it checks a single model-output property, not multiple agentic decisions in sequence.","test_description":"Run against the real embedding model used in production. For a fixed query, call embedding generation, assert returned vector length equals the live index dimension from vector DB metadata/config. Fail if mismatch.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.4,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The similarity search returns results ordered by descending cosine similarity score.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This behavior is about actual search-engine ordering semantics at the vector DB boundary. Real failures often come from ANN/index metric settings, DB-side scoring/ordering, or transport/serialization effects that mocks hide. Rejected lower levels (Unit/Integration): disqualified because they can validate local sorting logic but not real DB score ordering behavior. Rejected higher level (Agentic): disqualified by behavior text; it does not require validating AI output quality, only DB score ordering.","test_description":"Use a real vector DB instance/index configured as production metric=cosine. Insert controlled vectors with known relative cosine to a test query vector, execute similarity search through the API/repo layer, assert returned scores are monotonic non-increasing and IDs match expected order.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.55,"Agentic":0.07,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The LLM re-ranking step changes the order of at least some results compared to the raw similarity ranking when the query has nuanced intent.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real LLM judgment for nuanced intent. A mock re-ranker can trivially reorder and always pass, hiding failures where the real model does not meaningfully rerank. Rejected lower levels (System/Integration): disqualified because they only verify plumbing and cannot validate model-driven ranking behavior. Rejected higher level (Workflow): disqualified by behavior text; this is one agentic decision point (re-rank), not a multi-agentic pipeline correctness requirement.","test_description":"For a curated nuanced query + candidate set where raw similarity ranking is intentionally imperfect, call the real re-ranking model and assert returned order differs from raw order for at least one pair, with retry budget to account for model variance.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.7,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A query with no close matches in the database returns an empty result set rather than low-relevance noise.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"The pass/fail outcome depends on real embedding-space semantics plus thresholding; mocked vectors/scores can hide the real failure where model embeddings still pull weak neighbors and the system leaks noise. Behavior text is about real-query relevance outcome (\"no close matches\"), not just deterministic threshold code. Rejected lower levels (Integration/System): disqualified because they can pass with synthetic scores and miss model-dependent false positives. Rejected higher level (Workflow): disqualified because this checks one agentic relevance boundary, not multiple agentic handoffs.","test_description":"With the real embedding model and real vector DB, run out-of-domain/no-match queries against a fixture corpus. Assert API returns empty list when max similarity is below configured cutoff, and does not emit low-score filler items.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.5,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The end-to-end latency from receiving the query to returning re-ranked results stays below 2 seconds for the median case.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This behavior measures a full pipeline SLA across multiple sequential steps, including at least two model calls (embedding + LLM re-rank) plus vector search and API handling. By definition it is multi-step agentic. Rejected lower levels (Agentic/System/Integration): disqualified because isolating a single step cannot expose cumulative median latency breach across the full chain.","test_description":"Execute an end-to-end load scenario through the real API path using production-like dependencies (embedding service, vector DB, LLM re-ranker). Collect per-request latency over a representative sample and assert p50 < 2.0s.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.25,"Agentic":0.2,"Workflow":0.5}}]}
